ystem can reliably get the correct user plan data, regardless of timing.\n\n\n**Diagnosing Persistence Issues**\n\nMy current focus is on a potential data synchronization issue after user login, specifically in `library-state.js`. A race condition may be happening if data loading isn't complete when `getList()` is called, resulting in the paid plan being set incorrectly. My next step will be to confirm whether this is a consistent problem.\n\n\n**Diagnosing Persistence Issues**\n\nMy team is on the case of a stubborn bug. I've been focusing on how data loads after login. I'm starting to think about whether the way we load data from WebSim may have a race condition that leads to incorrect determinations of a user's plan.  I need to rethink how data is synchronized.\n\n\n**Addressing Stale Data**\n\nI'm now investigating a potential timing issue. While the recent code adjustments seem to work in some cases, the \"everyone has a paid plan\" issue persists in others. I'm suspecting the data loading strategy and trying to understand whether the user has persistence on the first load. My hypothesis is that there's a problem with stale data or an unexpected initialization state.\n\n\n\nlibrary-state.js\n\n```library-state.js\n```"
