          "yapping": "**Implementing UI changes**\n\nI need to craft a response that outlines the change: the apocalyptic decorative elements should only show when infections hit 50 million, while the non-infection UI stays in light mode until then. We already have a toggle for calm mode when infections are below 50 million, which puts a calm class on the UI. It seems we should adjust the CSS so that the dark red theme only appears when infections reach or exceed this threshold, while keeping everything calm prior.\n**Clarifying UI requirements**\n\nEarlier, the issue was that the text was green instead of red, which we fixed by adding a body.calm class for green text. Now, they want the non-infection UI to stay in light mode if infections are below a certain threshold. Decorative elements and the dark theme should only appear when infections hit or exceed 50 million. I wonder what \"it\" refers to—maybe the \"World Leaders Panel\" or \"Science mode\"? The body.calm class already hides decorations, but we may need to set the threshold for displaying elements more precisely for clarity.\n**Interpreting UI requirements**\n\nIt seems they want the elements to only show when infections hit exactly 50 million, so I'll keep the condition as greater than or equal. They also mentioned that some elements on the right panel still show red decorations, even in calm mode. The CSS takes care of many aspects, but there might be leftover red hints. I’ll check if the infected text should stay red while keeping the non-infection UI light. Currently, in calm mode, everything forces to green, including the infected count under 50 million, which they requested earlier.\n**Clarifying UI instructions**\n\nIt looks like they want the non-infection UI to remain light even if infections reach or exceed 50 million, which seems contradictory. The phrasing suggests they want apocalypse decorations to show only at that threshold while keeping the non-infection UI light. If I understand correctly, the right panel inputs and general UI elements should also stay light regardless. They've previously requested green text for counts below 50 million, so I’ll ensure calm mode stays until infections hit the threshold, but I’ll also check if calm mode toggles off when zero infected values are present, since our applyMood uses float values.\n**Implementing UI updates**\n\nThey want the non-infection UI to stay light even when infections reach 50 million, which seems contradictory. I'll clarify that the apocalypse decorations appear at that threshold while keeping the rest light. I’ll change the wording so calm mode is the default and hide decorations until that point. Additionally, we’ll adjust the CSS to ensure the right panel remains light-themed, independent of the calm state. I'll also explicitly set conditions to apply calm mode when infections are less than or equal to the threshold. Lastly, I’ll ensure the code updates follow these directives for clarity and consistency.\n\nI will keep the entire UI in light mode until infections reach 50 million, and ensure the right-side non-infection controls stay in light mode even after 50 million.\n\nstyles.css\n\n```styles.css\n```"
